The [https://github.com/tarsius/elm Emacs Lisp Mirror] is not yet available. Meanwhile the [[Git repository]] might give you some relieve. Once the [https://github.com/tarsius/elm Emacs Lisp Mirror] is available it will makes it easier to extend GNU Emacs by collecting Emacs lisp libraries in one location in an uniform way.

By commenting on [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/454259/what-do-you-expect-from-a-package-manager-for-emacs What do you expect from a package manager for Emacs] on stackoverflow.com you might influence the direction it will be taking.
